The paper proposes a method for 3D face reconstruction and recognition using an encoder-decoder network. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing and feature extraction, which suggests that cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with 3D modeling (cs.GR) and machine learning (cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI) techniques for training the network and measuring performance.
